      <div class="msgContentFrame">It is a broken system that I would recommend not using, unless you like sitting there and getting killed while your skills are not firing. <br /> <br />It needs some work, that is for sure. I have only seen it work &quot;perfectly&quot; a few times. But 90% of the time, it seems to be totally wonky and not work as the devs state it does. <br /> <br />But you can use &quot;G&quot; to turn it on (I think?) and off/execute. The button next to your hot bar also turns it on and off. Basically, you turn it on, people queue skills. Then someone hits the button again, and it's supposed to execute in the queued order. Except that it basically, never works. Especially in large groups, it just isn't going to happen. <br /> <br />And each person has to enter the battle regimen mode individually to queue up skills. Then any one person and execute it. Also, you can't attack/do anything when you are in BR mode, so make sure you are not actually fighting anything difficult, as you will literally be a sitting duck while you mess around with the BR's that are going to fail to execute anyways. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 11th 2010 11:37am by MattVid6 </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1385155" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1385155">[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png</a>[/img]</a></div></div>
